Company Policy Handbook — Sample Document

1. Working Hours

Employees are expected to work 9:00 AM to 6:00 PM, Monday to Friday.

A lunch break of 1 hour is allowed between 1:00 PM and 2:00 PM.

2. Leave Policy

Each employee is entitled to 18 paid leaves annually.

Prior approval from the reporting manager is mandatory before availing leave.

3. Code of Conduct

Maintain professionalism in workplace communication.

Use company resources responsibly.

Harassment, discrimination, or misuse of confidential data is strictly prohibited.

4. Remote Work

Employees may apply for remote work based on project requirements and manager approval.

The company reserves the right to revoke remote privileges at any time.

5. Security Guidelines

Use only company-approved devices and networks.

All passwords must comply with the IT department’s security standards.

6. Termination

Either party may terminate employment with one month’s written notice.

Misconduct may lead to immediate termination.

7. Contact

HR Department: hr@companyname.com

IT Support: itsupport@companyname.com
